The paper deals with revenue maximization in a setting where a seller has little prior information on demand and faces myopic buyers. This problem falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and optimization (cs.DS). The paper also uses techniques from machine learning (cs.MA) and information theory (cs.IT) to derive its results. Additionally, the paper discusses the influence of externalities on revenue maximization, which could potentially fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
